近藤大介：日本疫情可能进一步扩大。
Mr. Kondo: The epidemic is likely to spread further in Japan.
近藤大介2020-02-18 11:43。
Nippon Kondo 2020-02-18 11: 43
扫描二维码分享到朋友圈。
Scanning two-dimensional code to share with friends.
近藤大介/文 2月16日晚，日本厚生劳动大臣加藤胜信在记者招待会上无奈地表示：“目前，疫情正在逐渐发生变化。
"The epidemic is gradually changing," Kattori Kato, Japan's health minister, said at a news conference yesterday evening.
病毒的传染路径已经开始让人捉摸不透了……”。
The route of transmission of the virus is beginning to be elusive... "
就在当天下午的5点，日本政府组织召开了“新型冠状病毒对策专家会”的首次会议。
At 5 pm on the same day, the Japanese government organized the first meeting of the "Expert Meeting on New Coronavirus Countermeasures."
日本的病毒学和传染病学专家们齐聚一堂，共同商讨疫情对策。
Virology and epidemiology experts from Japan came together to discuss the response to the outbreak.
在会后举行的记者招待会上，日本国立传染病研究所所长脇田隆宇对疫情作了如下说明：。
At a press conference held after the meeting, the Director of the National Institute of Infectious Diseases, Tian Longyu, made the following statement on the epidemic:
“目前，日本已经出现了与武汉，甚至与整个中国无关的病例。
"There have been cases in Japan that have nothing to do with Wuhan or even China as a whole.
这是日本进入疫情初期的信号。
That is a sign that Japan is entering the early stages of the epidemic.
今后，疫情还有可能进一步扩大。
In the future, the epidemic is likely to spread further.
那么，如何合理使用医疗资源，将成为一个非常重要的问题。
Then, how to use the medical resource rationally, will become a very important question.
因为很多人只会经历‘由轻症到自愈’的过程，所以请大家先在家里调养。
Because many people will only go through the process of 'mild illness to self-healing', so please take care of yourself at home first.
如果出现了肺部不适的症状，再去医院就诊。
If you develop symptoms of lung discomfort, go to the hospital.
。
.
外出时，请利用‘错峰上下班’之类的方式，尽量避开人员密集或人流量大的场所。
When going out, please use 'staggered peak work' and other means, try to avoid the densely populated or heavy traffic places.
对于一些不重要、不紧急的集会，请慎重考虑必要性。
Think carefully about the necessity of assemblies that are not important or urgent.
”。
"
发言时，这位62岁的日本传染病学专家一直保持着平淡的口吻，但在场的所有人都听到一个非常恐怖的消息——禁止外出！大家都在心里嘀咕，难道日本会发生和中国同样的疫情？。
The 62-year-old expert on infectious disease in Japan kept his tone flat as he spoke, but everyone there heard the horrible news - no travel! Everyone wondered if Japan would have the same epidemic as China.
除了“严禁外出”，脇田隆宇在言辞中还透露了另一个恐怖的消息，那就是“如果出现了新型冠状病毒肺炎的症状，也不要去医院”。
In addition to "no travel," Tian Longyu in the standing menace of the speech also revealed another terrible news, that is "if the new coronavirus pneumonia symptoms, do not go to the hospital."
之所以不让疑似患者去医院，是因为全日本的专业医疗机构只能同时收治1800名患者。
Suspected patients are not allowed to go to hospitals because specialized medical institutions across Japan can only take in 1,800 patients at a time.
这个数字远远低于武汉紧急建成的火神山医院和雷神山医院的病床总数。
This figure is far below the total number of beds in Wuhan's emergency-built Fosen Mountain Hospital and Lei Shenshan Hospital.
。
.
2月18日，最近一段时间频繁出现在电视上的日本白鸥大学教授冈田春江在参加朝日电视台某节目录制时表示：“10天之后，日本的病例数也许会超过10万人。
"In 10 days' time, the number of cases in Japan may exceed 100,000," Okada Chunjiang, a professor at the University of Kitao, who appeared frequently on television on Feb. 18, told an Asahi TV program
”这句话让整个录制间一片哗然。
"The whole recording studio was in an uproar.
如果不幸被他预测中的话，日本就不会是“第二个中国”，而会是“第二个武汉”。
If, unfortunately, he predicted, Japan would not be "the second China," but "the second Wuhan."
。
.
在层出不穷的恐怖消息之中，停泊在横滨港内的豪华游轮“钻石公主号”上的人，终于收到了一个好消息。
Amid the ghastly news, the people on board the luxury ship, Princess Diamond, anchored in Yokohama harbour, finally got a good news.
。
.
此前，该游轮上一名中国香港乘客被确诊患有新型冠状病毒肺炎。
Earlier, a Hong Kong, China passenger on the cruise ship was diagnosed with a new coronavirus pneumonia.
截至2月17日发稿时止，已经确诊355名乘客被传染。
As of February 17, 355 passengers had been confirmed infected.
目前，全体乘客及船员（共计3711人）已经被强制隔离在船上将近两周。
At present, all passengers and crew (a total of 3,711) have been forced to stay on board the ship for nearly two weeks.
如果不出现意外情况，他们将在2月19日下船登岸。
If nothing unexpected happens, they will disembark on February 19th.
。
.
在隔离期间，船上的很多老年乘客都出现了严重的身体健康问题。
During the isolation, many of the elderly passengers on board developed serious health problems.
为此，怒不可遏的美国政府于本月16日打着“解救‘横滨泰坦尼克号’上的美国人”的旗号，派遣撤侨专机前往羽田机场，接走了近400名美国乘客。
The angry US government sent a special plane to Haneda airport on Monday under the banner of "rescuing the Americans aboard the Yokohama Titanic." Nearly 400 American passengers were picked up.
其他国家和地区，也准备效仿美国撤侨。
Other countries and regions are ready to follow suit.
。
.
现如今，世界各大媒体都把日本视为“紧跟在中国身后的危险国家”。
The world's media now view Japan as a "dangerous country close behind China."
对此，安倍政权可谓“苦不堪言”。
Abe's regime has been "miserable".
2011年3月，日本爆发福岛核危机，整个国家瞬间成为了“全球最危险的地方”。
When the Fukushima nuclear crisis erupted in Japan in March 2011, the country instantly became "the most dangerous place in the world."
经过了长达9年的努力，日本重新塑造了“安全、安心之都”的国际形象。
After nine years of efforts, Japan has remade its international image as a "safe and secure capital."
然而，正当所有日本人翘首期盼东京奥运会及残奥会到来的时候，日本又被贴上了“危险”的标签。
But just as all Japanese eagerly await the arrival of the Tokyo Olympics and Paralympics, Japan has been labeled "dangerous."
。
.
2月12日，也许是因为承受了超负荷的压力，日本首相安倍晋三在国会议事堂内丑态百出。
On February 12, Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe, perhaps under pressure from overloading, made a spectacle of himself in the Council Chamber.
在当天举行的众议院预算委员会上，在野党立宪民主党议员本清美向安倍提问：“您知道‘加吉鱼是从头部开始腐烂’这句话吗？”暗指日本政府之所以无力应对危机，是因为“为首”的安倍迂腐无能。
At a House Budget Committee meeting on the same day, opposition Democratic Constitutional Party member Ben Ching-mei asked Abe, "Do you know that the Japanese government's inability to cope with the crisis is due to the" first "Abe's pedantic incompetence.
本清美的话音刚落，在场的在野党成员纷纷拍手附和“没错，没错！”。
Benqing United States just said, the opposition members in the field clapped their hands to echo "Yes, yes!"
对于这般冷嘲热讽，安倍失去了他往日的平静心态。
Abe has lost his usual calm over such cynicism.
他愤怒地回答道：“这个问题毫无意义，我拒绝回答！”于是，本清美顺势再次发难：“既然如此，那是不是就只能换一个“为首”的人了？好吧，那我就当您马上就要退位了，我就不再问您问题了。
"The question is pointless," he replied angrily, "and I refuse to answer it." So, if so, isn't that just another "first" person? Well, then I'll assume you're about to abdicate and I won't ask you any more questions.
”就这样，当天的国会审议戛然而终。
In this way, the day's congressional deliberations ended with the conclusion of the case.
。
.
最终，安倍为自己的鲁莽行为付出了代价。
In the end, Abe paid the price for his reckless behavior.
2月17日早上，安倍在国会开始之时，就上周的事情向全体与会者鞠躬道歉。
On the morning of February 17, Abe bowed and apologized to all participants at the start of the parliamentary session about last week's events.
。
.
正所谓福无双至祸不单行，这一天安倍受到了双重重击：其一是新型冠状病毒肺炎的疫情；其二是共同通信社发布了今年2月的内阁支持率——由今年1月时的49.3%暴跌至41%。
On that day, Abe received a double whammy: the new coronavirus pneumonia; and the Common Coronavirus, which issued its cabinet approval rating in February, plummeted to 41% from 49.3% in January.
如果按照这个趋势继续发展的话，今年4月，安倍内阁的支持率就会跌破被誉为“政权危险线”的30%。
If this trend continues, Abe's cabinet will fall below 30% of what is known as the "danger line" in April.
。
.
同一天，日本内阁府发布了去年第四季度（2019年10月至12月）的GDP。
On the same day, Japan's cabinet announced GDP for the fourth quarter of last year (October-December 2019).
去年10月，安倍将日本的消费税由8%提升到了10%。
Last October, Abe raised Japan's consumption tax from 8% to 10%.
因此，所有人都在关注这项举措究竟会带来什么样的结果。
So everyone is watching to see what the outcome will be.
然而，让人大跌眼镜的是，经过年换算后得出的答案是“负6.3%”，大大超出了经济学家和分析家们的负面预期。
The big surprise, however, is that the answer after year-on-year conversion is "-6.3%," well above what economists and analysts had expected.
。
.
所有人都担心，在新型冠状病毒肺炎疫情的影响下，今年第一季度的GDP又会有怎样的结果。
Everyone fears what will happen to GDP in the first quarter of this year, given the impact of the new coronavirus pneumonia.
同时，很多人更加确信，持续了7年之久的安倍经济学已经彻底失效。
At the same time, many are more convinced that Abenomics, which has been going on for seven years, has completely failed.
。
.
安倍无论如何都要保护1.2亿国民的生命和安全。
Abe will, in any case, protect the lives and security of 120 million people.
因为这是他作为日本最高权力者应尽的基本职责。
For this is his basic duty as the highest authority in Japan.
然而，面对这一波由新型冠状病毒所引发的“超级海啸”，安倍政权还靠得住吗？。
But is Abe's regime credible in the face of this "super-tsunami" triggered by the new coronavirus?
对于这个问题，我很难自信地回答“YES”。
It is difficult for me to answer YES confidently.
上周，我和一位安倍的心腹大臣共进晚餐。
Last week, I had dinner with one of Abe's closest ministers.
对于他所关心的“中国的抗新冠病毒战争”，我可谓言无不尽。
I cannot say enough about his concern about China's war on the New Crown Virus.
但他只是默默的听着，偶尔会回应一句“哦”。
But he just listened in silence, occasionally responding to a "oh."
其实，我想表达的是，今天中国正在经历的战争，就是明天日本即将面对的战争。
In fact, I would like to express that the war China is going through today is the war Japan will face tomorrow.
至于这位大臣到底听懂了多少，估计只有他自己知道吧。
As for how much the minister understood, he must know it for himself.
。
.
回顾历史，我们不难发现，四面环海的岛国比大陆国家更容易获得和平。
Looking back at history, it is not difficult to see that island States surrounded by the sea find peace more easily than continental countries.
也许正是因为这个原因，自吴越战争和战国时代以来，日本经常是中国人的“战时避难所”。
Perhaps because of this, Japan has often been a "wartime refuge" for the Chinese since the Vietnam War and Warring States.
同样是因为这个原因，日本人的身体里根本不具备中国人有的“危机DNA”。
For the same reason, the Japanese do not have "crisis DNA" in their bodies at all.
安倍没有，下一任日本首相可能也不会有……。
Abe has not, and the next Japanese prime minister may not...
（作者系日本讲谈社《现代周刊》副主编，明治大学讲师。
(The writer is Deputy Editor-in-Chief of Modern Weekly and lecturer at Meiji University.
